<div>OpenBSD lacks an aio.h header.</div><div>configure knows this:</div><div><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0.8ex;border-left-width:1px;border-left-color:rgb(204,204,204);border-left-style:solid;padding-left:1ex">
$ grep aio.h configure.log <br>checking aio.h usability... no<br>checking aio.h presence... no<br>checking for aio.h... no</blockquote></div><div><br></div><div>Yet fbtl/posix is enabled, despite needing aio.h:</div><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin-top:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px;margin-left:0.8ex;border-left-width:1px;border-left-color:rgb(204,204,204);border-left-style:solid;padding-left:1ex">
checking if MCA component fbtl:posix can compile... yes</blockquote><div><br></div><div>I am guessing this problem will appear on any platform w/o aio.h.</div><div><br></div><div>I think is just a simple matter of requiring OPAL_HAVE_AIO_H when &quot;checking if component fbtl:posix can compile&quot;.</div>
